      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing on specific racial or ethnic backgrounds is a very narrow and often inaccurate way to define ultra-high-net-worth individuals. Instead, target individuals from established, globally recognized wealth centers, such as those in established European, North American, or specific East Asian business communities. These groups often have a deep appreciation for traditional luxury and heritage brands. Look for those with inherited wealth or those who have achieved success in highly traditional, powerful industries like finance or established industry leadership.",
